    <Instrument_Host>
        <name>Venera 3</name>
        <type>Spacecraft</type>
        <description>

The Venera 3 spacecraft comprised a carrier bus holding a descent
craft/lander to study Venus and interplanetary space during cruise. The
bus served as a communications relay for the lander. It carried TV
imaging, spectrometers, micrometeoroid detectors, energetic particle
sensors, ion traps, magnetometer, radio detector, and cosmic radio emission
receiver. The lander became the first craft to reach another planet's
surface.

        </description>
